BASF SE (BAS) , the worldâ€™s biggest chemical
company, may invest as much as 6 billion euros ($7.45 billion)
in  emerging markets  by 2015 amid economic uncertainty in Europe,
 Tagesspiegel  reported, citing an interview with board member
Michael Heinz.  The company plans to spend 15 billion euros globally by
2015, 30 percent to 40 percent of it in emerging markets, Heinz
told the newspaper. Between 2016 and 2020, investment may rise
to as much as 20 billion euros, 35 percent to 45 percent of
which may be in emerging markets, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
